  <p>
    Thats crazy, the only pizza that could support that much sauce would be a deep dish pizza like the ones from Chicago. If you were to apply that much sauce to a thin crust pizza it would be a mess. Now, for pizza purest I recommend Antica Pizzeria in Marina Del Rey, true Neopolitan pizza. Try the Pizza Conection for deep dish pizza. One more might be Mullberry Street Pizza - Encino or Beverly Hills.<br/><br/>Most of the pizza sauce in Southern Cal is to acidic, they don't use the right tomatoes. Good luck.
  </p>
  
  

