  <p>
    I, too, am a pizza sauce devotee.  Village Pizzeria on Larchmont Boulevard (between Beverly and 3rd) has a pretty decent sauce and will put extra on your pizza if you ask (they don't gripe about it or charge extra, I believe... but you do have to ask).  I got a thin crust with extra sauce once and while it was a gloopy mess, it was quite tasty.  They also have a Sicilian crust which might support the extra sauce better, but I cannot vouch for it personally.<br/><br/>I haven't had much good pizza sauce recently, but i'll start paying attention to which one has the best.  <br/><br/>(Thought i'd mention that I love Little Caesar's &quot;crazy sauce,&quot; so YMMV)
  </p>
  
  

